Solidworks can open many CAD files. Sometimes you just need to make sure the settings are correct for your file.
I know I’ve used STEP, parasolid (.x_b), Inventor parts, and several other file types. The only thing I can remember not working is a CATIA file (which is a Dassault Systemes program as is Solidworks, go figure).
This may help:
https://help.solidworks.com/2021/english/SolidWorks/sldworks/c_Importing-Exporting_SOLIDWORKS_Documents.htm?id=6a2f816c29014f46b499becd6f6b3e4a#Pg0
